description:
&lt;p&gt;Would you like to be a part of an innovative and supportive team driving high standards of patient care? We are looking for nurses who enjoy nursing patients with a variety of medical conditions. Elderly Care is currently the most high profile work stream requiring highly skilled specialists in complex care management. You can develop skills in: Trauma, Urology, Nutrition, Tissue Viability, Respiratory, Dementia, Neurology, Stroke, Cardiology, Complex Discharge Planning and much more.&lt;br /&gt;We welcome newly qualified as well as experienced nurses to our acute medicine teams and provide you with an opportunity to learn and develop a variety of specialist skills and knowledge. We offer many benefits including:&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;- Comprehensive 18 months Preceptorship for newly qualified nurses.&lt;br /&gt;- On-going support from award winning team, Clinical Practice Educator, Clinical Nurse Specialists, Consultants and Allied Healthcare Professionals&lt;br /&gt;- Individually tailored career development pathways&lt;br /&gt;- Learning and development opportunities including access to mentorship and leadership courses as well as courses related to area of specialty including: Spinal Cord Injuries Training; Acutely unwell adult Course; ECG training &lt;br /&gt;- Internal transfer scheme (after 9 months)&lt;br /&gt;- Rotation opportunities including a variety of specialities&lt;br /&gt;- Accommodation&lt;br /&gt;- Nurseries and childcare vouchers&lt;br /&gt;- Keep Fit schemes&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Care of Elderly Wards are receiving Awards due to good practice every year. Do you want to be part of something that is innovative and celebrated? Then join us!&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;We support flexible working.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further information or to arrange an informal visit pleasecontact:&lt;br /&gt;Chito Gabutin, Ward Manager&lt;br /&gt;e-mail: chito.gabutin@nhs.net or call 0207 7794 0500 Ext 36757&lt;/p&gt;
